<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000, 9100, 9200, 9400, AND 9900 MODELS - CHASSIS ACCESSORIES -
        TROUBLESHOOTING - Truck Body Connection
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Truck Body Connection</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Marker Lights Power Feed</title>
            <table id="t0820202" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Marker Lights Power Feed</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.68in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.89in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.85in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.41in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Remove trailer marker lights relay from connector (463-R8). Turn key on and place
                                    headlight switch and cab and trailer lights switch in on position. Measure voltage
                                    at circuit 58C to gnd.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>(463) /R8, 58C to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 58C or cab light circuitry, then
                                    repair. Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s08191_250.xml" xrefid="x0820201">Trailer Connection</hotlnk>for
                                    feed circuit troubleshooting.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At (463-R8) measure voltage from circuit 58C to 58-GA.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>(463)/R8, 58C to 58-GA.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 58-GA or 11-G, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Remove fuse F3-A and check for open condition.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>F3-A.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then correct. Replace fuse.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Re-install fuse F3-A and at the fuse and circuit 14E measure voltage to gnd.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>F3-A, 14E to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuits 14H and 14E, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>With trailer marker lights relay still removed, measure voltage from circuit 58D
                                    to 58-GA.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>(463)/R8, 58D to 58-GA.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 58D, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Disconnect halves of connector (43), then with a test lead jumper circuit 58D to
                                    circuit 58R.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Measure voltage to gnd. at connector (43), circuit 58R.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>(43), 58R to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 58R, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Remove jumper and re-install trailer marker light relay. Then move headlight and
                                    cab and trailer lights switch to on position.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>9.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (43) circuit 58S, measure voltage to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>(43), 58S to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace faulty trailer marker lights relay.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>10.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Turn headlight switch off, reconnect (43) and turn headlight switch back on.
                                    Measure voltage to gnd. at terminal 2 of truck body junction block.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Truck body junction block, 2 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Marker light circuit checks good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 58S, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Ground Circuit</title>
            <table id="t0820203" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Ground Circuit</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.51in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.56in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.73in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.55in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Measure resistance from left dash gnd. stud to terminal 1 of truck body junction
                                    block.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Gnd stud to truck body junction block 1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>&#60;2 ohms</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Junction block gnd. circuit checks good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuits 11-GM, 11-GN, and 11-GI, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
